  "name": "Reverse-Feint",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/races/orc.png",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>You can goad an opponent into attacking you in order to make your counter attack all the more powerful.</em><br /><br /><strong>Prerequisites</strong><br />Toughness, base attack bonus +1, orc.<br /><br /><strong>Benefits</strong><br />As a move action, you can leave a gap in your defenses for one adjacent opponent to use. If the opponent attacks you on its next turn, it gains a +4 bonus on its attack roll. Whether or not the opponent successfully hits, you may attack it as an immediate action with a single melee attack, gaining a +2 bonus on your attack roll.<br /><br /></p>\n<p><strong>Combat Trick</strong></p>\n<p>You can spend 2 stamina points to make the attack granted by this feat as a free action rather than an immediate action. You can still make the attack only once per use of this feat.</p>",
